entries.meaning: The fine particles (dust) created by sawing wood or other material.

verbs.description: sawdust (third-person singular simple present sawdusts, present participle sawdusting, simple past and past participle sawdusted)

examples: […]  the raking out of yesterday's fire, the kindling of to-day's under the collegiate boiler, the filling of that Spartan vessel at the pump, the sweeping and sawdusting of the common room, and other such preparations.
